Paper: hep-th/9204026

Date: 1992-04-10

Title: Dilaton Gravity and No-Hair Theorem in Two Dimensions

Authors: Olaf Lechtenfeld and Chiara Nappi

Comments: 11 pages, no figures, macropackage=phyzzx

Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B288 (1992) 72-76

We study a general class of two-dimensional theories of the dilaton-gravitytype inspired by string theory and show that they admit chargedmultiple-horizon black holes. These solutions are proved to satisfy scalarno-hair theorems.